  "issue_number": 1677,
  "issue_title": "[Card Bug] Layer 6 static ability `affected` filters with `FilterProp::PtComparison` evaluate against base P/T, not final computed P/T \u2014 affected set is wrong whenever Layer 7 effects are active (CR 613.1 + CR 613.8a)",
  "issue_body": "### Card(s)\n\nSiege Behemoth, April O'Neil, Questing Beast (CantBeBlockedBy subclass), Inspiring Commander, and any card whose continuous static ability grants an effect to creatures matching a power/toughness threshold\n\n### Build/version\n\n_No response_\n\n### Game mode\n\nAI\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe `depends_on` function in `crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs` implements CR 613.8a dependency detection with only **two axes**:\n\n1. If effect B **changes types** \u2192 effect A depends on B when A's affected filter references a card type (`filter_references_type`).\n2. If effect B **adds/removes abilities** \u2192 effect A depends on B when A's affected filter references an ability keyword (`filter_references_ability`).\n\n**The third required axis is absent:**\n\n> If effect B **modifies power/toughness** (via `ContinuousModification::AddPower`, `AddToughness`, `SetPowerDynamic`, `SetToughnessDynamic`, etc.) \u2192 effect A depends on B when A's **`affected_filter`** contains `FilterProp::PtComparison`.\n\nBecause of this gap, effects in `Layer::SetPT` that have a `PtComparison` affected filter are applied in **timestamp order** rather than after the P/T-modifying effects that determine which objects they actually apply to. This produces wrong game states.\n\nCompounding the problem: **`Layer::ModifyPT` has `has_dependency_ordering() == false`** (see `crates/engine/src/types/layers.rs:200`). Any conditional `ModifyPT` effect (e.g., a lord that only buffs creatures already at power 4+) is applied in pure timestamp order, with no dependency pass. If an unconditional `ModifyPT` lord was put on the battlefield before the conditional lord, the unconditional lord has a lower timestamp and is applied first \u2014 correctly. But if it was put on the battlefield *after* the conditional lord, it has a higher timestamp, is applied second, and the conditional lord (applied first) computed its affected set *before* the unconditional lord boosted the creatures. This silently produces the wrong set of creatures.\n\n---\n\n## Concrete reproduction\n\n### Scenario A \u2014 Layer::SetPT (dependency ordering is enabled, but P/T axis is absent)\n\n1. Put creature A on the battlefield: printed as a 4/4.  \n2. At timestamp T1, a continuous effect enters: *\"Each creature with power 5 or greater becomes a 1/1\"* (`SetPT`, `affected` = `PtComparison { Power, GE, 5 }`, timestamp T1).\n3. At timestamp T2 > T1, a second continuous effect enters: *\"All creatures become 6/6\"* (`SetPT`, unconditional, timestamp T2).\n\n**Current result (timestamp order, no P/T dependency axis):**\n- T1 applies first: creature A has power 4 \u2192 4 < 5 \u2192 not affected. Creature A stays at whatever base.\n- T2 applies second: creature A becomes 6/6.\n- Final: 6/6.\n\n**Correct result (CR 613.8a dependency order):**\n- T2 should apply first because T1's affected set *depends on* T2's outcome (T2 sets creature A to 6/6, which now qualifies for T1's \u2265 5 threshold).\n- T2: creature A \u2192 6/6.\n- T1: creature A power is now 6 \u2265 5 \u2192 becomes 1/1.\n- Final: 1/1.\n\nThe engine produces 6/6; CR 613.8a requires 1/1.\n\n### Scenario B \u2014 Layer::ModifyPT (dependency ordering is entirely disabled)\n\n1. Put creature B on the battlefield: printed as a 3/3.\n2. At timestamp T1, a conditional lord enters: *\"Creatures you control with power 4 or greater get +2/+0\"* (`ModifyPT`, `affected` = `PtComparison { Power, GE, 4 }`).\n3. At timestamp T2 > T1, an unconditional lord enters: *\"All creatures you control get +2/+0\"* (`ModifyPT`, unconditional).\n\n**Current result (pure timestamp order, no dependency pass):**\n- T1 (conditional lord, older): creature B power = 3 < 4 \u2192 no effect.\n- T2 (unconditional lord, newer): creature B power +2 \u2192 5/3.\n- Final: 5/3 (conditional lord never fires because its check ran before T2 boosted the creature).\n\n**Correct result per CR 613.8a:**\n- Unconditional T2 changes the affected set of conditional T1 (boosting creature B to 5+ makes it qualify for T1). T1 depends on T2.\n- T2 applies first: creature B \u2192 5/3.\n- T1 applies: power is now 5 \u2265 4 \u2192 +2 \u2192 7/3.\n- Final: 7/3.\n\nThe engine produces 5/3; CR 613.8a requires 7/3.\n\n---\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCR 613.8a states: *\"An effect is dependent on another effect if it's applied in the same layer or sublayer and, after applying one effect, the other effect would affect a different set of objects.\"* The second effect must be applied first.\n\nFor `Layer::SetPT` and `Layer::ModifyPT`: any effect A whose `affected_filter` contains `FilterProp::PtComparison` must be ordered **after** every same-layer effect B whose `modification` variant modifies power or toughness (AddPower, AddToughness, SetPowerDynamic, SetToughnessDynamic, AddDynamicPower, AddDynamicToughness, etc.), whenever applying B changes which objects A applies to.\n\n---\n\n## Root cause\n\n### Gap 1 \u2014 `depends_on` missing third axis (`crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs`)\n\nThe function currently ends after two checks:\n\n```rust\nfn depends_on(a: &ActiveContinuousEffect, b: &ActiveContinuousEffect, _state: &GameState) -> bool {\n    // ... same-source guard ...\n    // ... CopyValues unconditional dependency ...\n\n    let b_changes_types = matches!(&b.modification, ContinuousModification::AddType { .. } | ...);\n    if b_changes_types && filter_references_type(&a.affected_filter) { return true; }\n\n    let b_changes_abilities = matches!(&b.modification, ContinuousModification::AddKeyword { .. } | ...);\n    if b_changes_abilities && filter_references_ability(&a.affected_filter) { return true; }\n\n    false   // \u2190 missing third axis here\n}\n```\n\nThe missing third axis:\n```rust\n    let b_changes_pt = matches!(\n        &b.modification,\n        ContinuousModification::AddPower { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::AddToughness { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::AddDynamicPower { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::AddDynamicToughness { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::SetPowerDynamic { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::SetToughnessDynamic { .. }\n            | ContinuousModification::SetBasePT { .. }\n    );\n    if b_changes_pt && filter_references_pt_stat(&a.affected_filter) { return true; }\n```\n\n### Gap 2 \u2014 `Layer::ModifyPT` has no dependency pass (`crates/engine/src/types/layers.rs`)\n\n```rust\nassert!(!Layer::ModifyPT.has_dependency_ordering());  // line 200\n```\n\n`has_dependency_ordering()` returns `false` for `ModifyPT`, so `order_with_dependencies` is never called for Layer 7c effects. Every conditional `ModifyPT` effect with a `PtComparison` affected filter is therefore permanently broken by design.\n\n---\n\n## Files requiring changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs` | Add `fn filter_references_pt_stat(filter: &TargetFilter) -> bool` (mirrors `filter_references_type`/`filter_references_ability`); add third axis to `depends_on`; add `b_changes_pt` variant set |\n| `crates/engine/src/types/layers.rs` | Enable `has_dependency_ordering()` for `Layer::ModifyPT`; update the match arm; add `Layer::ModifyPT` to the `has_dependency_ordering` true-branch alongside `Layer::SetPT` |\n| `crates/engine/src/game/filter.rs` | Add `filter_references_pt_stat` (or export a helper) that detects `FilterProp::PtComparison` within a `TargetFilter`; update `affected_filter_uses_object_population` to treat `PtComparison` as a population-sensitive axis in the incremental escalation check |\n| `crates/engine/src/types/ability.rs` | Enumerate all `ContinuousModification` variants that produce P/T changes for the `b_changes_pt` match in `depends_on`; cross-check `ContinuousModification::layer()` in `types/layers.rs` |\n| `crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs` (tests) | Add unit tests: `pt_modification_dependency_overrides_timestamp_in_set_pt_layer`, `pt_modification_dependency_overrides_timestamp_in_modify_pt_layer`, `conditional_lord_applies_after_unconditional_lord_at_lower_timestamp`, `no_spurious_self_dependency_for_same_source_pt_and_filter` |\n| `crates/engine/src/game/layers.rs` (`incremental_flush_must_escalate`) | Treat an entered object that carries a `ModifyPT` or `SetPT` effect with a `PtComparison` affected filter as an escalation trigger, since re-ordering is now required for the full board |\n\n---\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n**Scenario B** is easiest to set up in goldfish mode:\n\n1. Begin a Solo/goldfish game.\n2. Cast a 3/3 creature (e.g., a 3/3 Bear token via command).\n3. Cast a conditional lord with the Oracle text *\"Creatures you control with power 4 or greater get +2/+0\"* (any such card or a custom scenario).\n4. Cast an unconditional lord *\"All creatures you control get +2/+0\"* **after** the conditional lord (so it has a higher timestamp).\n5. Check the Bear's power: should be 7 (3 base + 2 from unconditional lord \u2192 qualifies for conditional lord \u2192 +2 more). Engine shows 5.\n\n---\n\n### Logs/screenshots/game-state\n\n_No response_",
